RIP BEAVIS (2013?-2023). my pet parrotlet, beavis, passed away yesterday. from the beginning when i rehomed him on christmas day 2014, he was always a fighter. sometimes quick to temper, but always lasting in love. three years ago he had a growth near his nasal passage, which was removed, became infected, and eventually healed after weeks of antibiotic shots. it left a large hole in his left nose. the new skin closed and left him with only the right nostril to fully breathe. but he fought thru it and thrived, claiming several areas of the living room as his territory. last year he got into another fight w butthead which resulted in a hole in his beak, but it healed and the beak grew back fully. every few months he had some sort of health challenge, but he always came thru. while beavis never had a female partner (only his brother, butthead, to play with), he enjoyed the company of my slippers. he always shared food with his brother, and would be the first to preen him, but often his picking would be too hard and elicit a quick bite back from butthead. when he was done, he would turn his head sideways looking for butthead to return the favor, but it was seldom returned. beavis started to learn to fly to my finger on call, but as always only if i had a treat in my other hand. he loved shrimp, octopus, sunflower and chia seeds the most. the house will be quieter now that he is gone. in the end, his bites were not as vicious as before. and he was always a fighter. #parrotlets #beavisandbutthead

MONKEY PRINCE #12. final issue of our limited series hits shelves today for new comic book day. it’s been a two year journey w the team and one that’s been a dream-come-true project. from the moment editor @jesschillin_likeavillain brought me in, to the final brush stroke on the paper, this has been one of the most memorable titles since i started my professional career over 30 years ago — i mean, we introduced the actual MONKEY KING, SUN WUKONG, and all of the JOURNEY TO THE WEST, as well as MARCUS SUN, aka MONKEY PRINCE, into the dc universe alongside batman, robin, aquaman and supergirl!!! congratulations to our genius team of @geneluenyang @mmaiolo @sebastianchengcolor @thejanicechiang wes abbott @haining_art @tancomics @sotocolor — and my deepest gratitude to all of you who followed and read along. what started as a novel concept blossomed into a character and storyline that has impacted the entire dc universe. and while this may be the final issue of our first limited series, it certainly only marks the beginning of many more stories and escapades for shifu pigsy, shelli, sun wukong, and the muthaflippin’ monkey prince!!! #monkeyprince #dccomics #dcu #dcuniverse #journeytothewest #sunwukong #pigsy #comics #comicbooks

social_posts.post_text: MONKEY PRINCE #12. as any professional comic book artist will attest, we’ve worked in many strange places. from the comfort of our home studios, to literally planes, trains and automobiles. to empty overnight airport terminals, to cold hard overnight bathrooms while your significant other sleeps in the warm hotel bed, to the subway on the way to delivering pages in person, and any other number of exotic and unusual places - so as long as there is a flat surface and a deadline. these last two years on monkey prince has taken me around the world meeting fans and friends in three continents and over a handful of countries. i hope to travel more this year and explore even more, absorbing as much as i can in each new environment, and bringing those experiences and passion back into my work. thank you again for all of your support thru monkey prince. we’ve only just begun!!! #monkeyprince #dccomics #dcu #dcuniverse #comicbooks #comics #comicbookartist #journeytothewest #monkeyking

FIGURE DRAWING. always important to get back to basics every now and then and sharpen the blade… quick one/three/five/ten/fifteen minute poses. the first few sketches were gestures, and really just me getting use to various brush options on procreate. the latter three were a bit longer in time but as with live drawing, you still have to be quick and observant as the human model will eventually move and shift over longer periods of time. i started drawing from live nude models in high school, and am a big proponent of young artists drawing from real life as opposed to just pictures. this is my first time drawing from a model on zoom, which presented its own challenges, but i think it’s still kinda incredible that i get to sit in my own studio and draw a live model broadcasting from an art studio halfway across the planet in spain! @lifedrawingbarcelona #figuredrawing #artmodel #figuresketch #procreate #artschool

BOOKWORM. my family immigrated to the states when i was six, i didn’t speak a lick of english. by second grade in ms hazard’s class, i had read the most number of books out of all second graders. the one book that still lives rent free in my memories is RUNT OF ROGERS SCHOOL. not the literary masterpiece by any means, and weird how the word “runt” is like rarely used in modern day conversations, but funny how a silly book about a short kid in middle america overcame tremendous odds to star in his football team has carved out its own little corner in my brain. are there any books from your childhood that you still remember? #bookworm #batman #darkknight #dccomics #dcu #dcuniverse #batmanvillains #gotham #comicbookart #inksketch #runt #runtofrogersschool

JEAN GREY #1. after months of production, today is the day our hard work and effort is released. no more looking back. no more revisions or patches. today i get to be on a book with one of the comic book industry’s legendary writers @louisesimonson926 - i also get to share this moment w the modern day master and my brother-at-arms, @mmaiolo . i hope you enjoy this first of four issues. it was definitely a time warp for me, bringing up memories of my teenage years when i first carefully laid down that copy of UNCANNY XMEN and flipped thru each page one by one, and forever mesmerized by this tale of mutants fighting for humanity, and their own struggle for survival, acceptance and love. i’m some ways, y out could say that the phoenix saga was the first romance story i read — and it all started w jean grey… #jeangrey #marvelcomics #mcu #uncannyxmen #xmen #comicbooks #phoenix

ROGUE. fantasy football has officially kicked off with some surprising results in week one. in all three leagues, my teams were projected to lose badly, but as the universe would have it, i ended up winning all three games. last year i was projected win most of my games and ended up losing most of them. are there repercussions to lackluster fantasy projections? like do computer algorithms get replaced w new ones? what if in the future an algorithm gets too popular but has a bad week predicting results and gets shuts down and in an attempt to preserve its own life fights back and creates the terminator universe? i guess we’re better off forgetting it was horrible at picking how many yards a receiver would get. how did your team do? #rogue #xmen #marvelcomics #pencilsketch

PRATT BASKETBALL. it’s that fabled time of the year — the start of the college basketball season!!! congrats to everyone who put in the sweat and tears working on their game, building up their conditioning, getting stronger in the weight room, watching game tape to look for areas of improvement, shooting free throw after free throw, gritting thru those line touches, and finishing the layup on those three-man weaves. now is when you put all that effort into something that counts. now is when every shot taken, assist made, turnover, rebound, foul, and minute stepped onto that court gets recorded in the stat book for all of HISTORY. putting on the jersey of the school that played in the first ever nyc area collegiate basketball game, won the national championship in 1901, made four naia postseason appearances and two ecac tournaments, first ever woman to play in a men’s ncaa game, a former player drafted by the knicks, and a streetball legend named half-man half-amazing. may you play every game with heart, passion and honor. stay injury free. guys who get playing time, make the most of every second on the court. guys on the bench, cheer your guys on and always be focused and ready to keep up the energy when you do get in. and when you win, celebrate as if you’ve been there before. if you lose, pick yourself up and come back to fight the next day. your fellow teammates are your brothers for life now, as are the lettermen who donned those same jerseys and numbers. listen to your coaches. and wear that black and gold with pride. JIA YOU! @prattmensbasketball @goprattgo @prattwbb #prattbasketball #collegebasketball

JEAN GREY #4. our final installment in the journey behind one of the original xmen, jean grey, after she was killed in the hellfire gala, and finds herself in the white hot room, exploring her various life choices. such a pleasure to work with one of the legendary creators responsible for so many of my cherished comics stories from my youth, @louisesimonson926 and to continue my collaboration with the best in the industry, @mmaiolo . thank you to the crew at marvel for this opportunity. and above all, thank YOU for everyone who supported and read and enjoyed the series. it was so awesome to work in the old marvel plot style, and really capture the essence of comics storytelling, thru one of the most beloved marvel xmen characters. the team, along with the many cover artists like @amyreedercomics really put our heart and souls into this one as we all understand how dear and true jean grey is to you and your love of the medium. #jeangrey #xmen #marvelcomics #hellfiregala #whitehotroom #comicbookart

KEITH GIFFEN. happy birthday to the late great, keith giffen. i first met @therealgiffen at the valiant offices one summer afternoon when publisher steve massarsky was showing him around. months later we would be collaborating on a short story in his irrelevant series PUNX, featuring a satire on the 90s “bad girls” era of comics, called “bernard chang in conjunction with bernard chang enterprises presents a bernard chang production of bernard chang’s bad babes with butts to die for.” as a commentary on the oversaturation of scantily-clad female characters, keith wanted to do a short story where we just drew shots of rear ends. i think we did two stints of the spoof (not sure if the second version ever saw print), two issues of xo manowar, and an unfinished/unpublished batman legends of the dark knight four-issue story for dc. keith, being a legendary artist himself, wrote his scripts/plots in a rather unique way of actual 6 to 9 panel page rough layouts w dialogue balloons attached, as opposed to the regular format of a word document. he gave me the ultimate freedom to change up the layouts, so as along as the story and dialogue remained relatively the same. he is credited as the co-creator of lobo, ambush bug and rocket raccoon, as well as a writer/artist on a long list of acclaimed titles. keith passed away on october 9th, and today would’ve been his 71st birthday. rest in peace, keith.

JEAN GREY. one of my favorite moments from our limited series featuring our favorite x-men was that i had the opportunity to bookend the story with mirror images. my initial concept was to start the series with an upside down image of jean, in a daze and bathed in uncertainty, and ending with her at peace and assured. because the issues were drawn months apart, it wasn’t a given i would have the opportunity to complete the initial idea, but the stars aligned and we @louisesimonson926 @mmaiolo were able to pull off the feat. it’s a minor detail to most readers, but as a storyteller, i just love putting the bow tie on the ribbon after wrapping the gift. #jeangrey #marvelcomics #xmen #comicbooks
